I went from having someone I could talk to 24/7, someone who would always fight for me, someone who was down just to sit in silence with me just bc I needed someone. That whole summer without him I felt like I was drowning and when I finally saw him, I could breathe again.
Max had been trying to date me for four years and I continuously shot him down, he went to Japan for a couple weeks and then went to Virginia for a month and I was having a stressful summer

At this point I was dead sure I didnt have feelings so I told him that we would never be more than friends and basically tried to make it super clear that nothing would ever happen and we went and had a great time all that

Max immediately offered to take me instead, he said hed buy the tickets off me, he just wanted me to be happy and have a good time. I knew if we went it would cross a line of being friends and something more so I set down ground rules.

Senior year he took me to homecoming but we went as friends and we had a really good time, we spent so much time together and most of it was spent by me complaining about the loser guy I was dating at the time. The day I bought prom tickets I found out he was cheating on me

The rest of high school I dated other ppl & whenever I wasnt dating someone he would try to get back in the ring but at that point it was hard determining how I actually felt about him, I didnt know if it was a friendship or actual feelings but it was scary so we stayed friends

He went to Virginia over the summer and we didnt talk bc he didnt have phone service so I got bored and we just kinda... fell off. Neither of us really talked about what happened but I started dating someone else so that kinda determined things

So he asked me on a date like the end of freshman year, I agreed, we went bike racing and it was cool but neither of us had really been on a date before so it was kinda awkward and his parents were there bc neither of us could drive

We met freshman year, were both from Virginia, had similar music tastes, had some classes, etc. I was taller than him, his voice was higher than mine, just a couple of awkward teens who obviously liked each other and everyone saw it but us and our friends would call us out but ya
